  "prompt": "Can I make a voice call from my iPad using Jio SIM?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff date in October 2023, iPads generally do not support traditional voice calls directly using a SIM card, including Jio SIMs, because they lack the necessary phone app and cellular voice calling capabilities that are present in smartphones. However, you can use your Jio SIM for data services on your iPad and make voice calls using various apps that offer VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol) services. Here are a few options:\n\n1. **JioCall App**: If Jio offers a dedicated app for making calls using data, you can use this app to make voice calls over the internet. Check the App Store for any official Jio apps that might support this feature.\n\n2. **FaceTime**: If the person you are calling also has an Apple device, you can use FaceTime for voice and video calls over the internet.\n\n3. **Other VoIP Apps**: You can use apps like WhatsApp, Skype, Google Duo, or Zoom to make voice and video calls over the internet. These apps work using your data connection, which can be provided by your Jio SIM.\n\nTo use these services, ensure your Jio SIM is activated for data and that your iPad is configured to use mobile data. If you need further assistance on setting up your Jio SIM for data use on your iPad, you may need to contact Jio customer support or refer to their official guidelines.",
